WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.000
========================CHAPTERS AND OPENINGS=====================

3
00:01:54.760 --> 00:02:01.680
Dorry and Brogy

4
00:02:08.690 --> 00:02:10.440
Huh? A-Are you okay?

5
00:02:12.820 --> 00:02:13.990
Whoa...

6
00:02:13.990 --> 00:02:15.900
They're so huge!

7
00:03:04.620 --> 00:03:06.670
H-He blocked the blow
with his helmet!

8
00:03:07.040 --> 00:03:10.130
If he was off by even a hair,
he would've died instantly!

9
00:03:26.770 --> 00:03:28.860
What a fight...!

10
00:03:29.360 --> 00:03:34.990
Each of their attacks is a lethal blow
aimed at their opponent's vital point!

11
00:03:34.990 --> 00:03:39.900
Those two have continued this
duel to the death for 100 years?

12
00:03:41.620 --> 00:03:43.120
But that's good news for us!

13
00:03:43.120 --> 00:03:44.870
Now we can escape.

14
00:03:44.870 --> 00:03:46.080
Let's go!

15
00:03:55.840 --> 00:03:57.010
Usopp?

16
00:04:00.340 --> 00:04:01.720
Incredible...

17
00:04:03.510 --> 00:04:05.600
Reason?

18
00:04:05.600 --> 00:04:07.100
I don't remember.

19
00:04:14.150 --> 00:04:17.860
They fight for no reason,
and yet they're so serious...

20
00:04:19.240 --> 00:04:21.450
I know! How exhausting, right?

21
00:04:21.450 --> 00:04:22.580
You don't get it!

22
00:04:23.080 --> 00:04:26.290
This is what a battle
between real men is all about!

23
00:04:27.710 --> 00:04:28.660
Meaning?

24
00:04:29.620 --> 00:04:36.670
To use an analogy, they each fly
a warrior's flag in their hearts,

25
00:04:36.670 --> 00:04:40.300
and those flags are more
important to them than life itself.

26
00:04:41.260 --> 00:04:43.430
They would never
let them be torn down.

27
00:04:43.430 --> 00:04:47.930
And so, to protect these flags,
they've fought for 100 years!

28
00:04:51.440 --> 00:04:52.690
Now do you get it?

29
00:04:52.690 --> 00:04:57.740
This is an honorable battle
between true warriors!

30
00:04:59.950 --> 00:05:00.700
Whatever.

31
00:05:01.280 --> 00:05:03.660
Stuff like that
doesn't interest me.

32
00:05:03.660 --> 00:05:04.620
Now, hurry up!

33
00:05:05.030 --> 00:05:06.580
I'm gonna watch a bit longer.

34
00:05:09.160 --> 00:05:14.630
They embody exactly what I want:
to be a brave warrior of the sea!

35
00:05:15.130 --> 00:05:18.590
I wanna be as honorable as them!

36
00:05:26.850 --> 00:05:28.850
So you want to be a giant.

37
00:05:29.770 --> 00:05:30.560
What the hell?!

38
00:05:31.100 --> 00:05:33.100
Were you even listening to me?!

39
00:05:33.100 --> 00:05:33.860
Look!

40
00:05:33.860 --> 00:05:36.070
Weren't you going to watch them?

41
00:05:41.950 --> 00:05:45.030
If there's a village
full of warriors like them,

42
00:05:45.030 --> 00:05:47.620
I wanna go there someday.

43
00:06:01.970 --> 00:06:07.680
We both long for home,
don't we, Dorry?

44
00:06:09.270 --> 00:06:15.810
That's why I'll beat you
and go back to Elbaph, Brogy.

45
00:06:31.160 --> 00:06:34.710
That's 73,466 duels...

46
00:06:35.120 --> 00:06:39.710
...and 73,466 draws.

47
00:07:06.700 --> 00:07:08.280
Hey, you overgrown lizard.

48
00:07:08.870 --> 00:07:10.240
Out of our way.

49
00:07:12.580 --> 00:07:14.160
Leave it to me.

50
00:07:16.670 --> 00:07:18.630
10,000 Kilo Press!

51
00:07:31.890 --> 00:07:34.480
Greetings, Mr. 5.

52
00:07:36.190 --> 00:07:40.980
Nice ability you've got there,
building an instant cottage in the jungle.

53
00:07:40.980 --> 00:07:44.320
Let's be clear, though.
This mission is still ours.

54
00:07:44.320 --> 00:07:46.700
We'd appreciate you staying out of it.

55
00:07:46.700 --> 00:07:49.450
We won't make
the same mistake twice.

56
00:07:49.450 --> 00:07:50.950
“Mistake”?

57
00:07:50.950 --> 00:07:52.620
That's incorrect.

58
00:07:52.620 --> 00:07:57.790
The two of you, Mr. 5
and Miss Valentine, are weak.

59
00:08:00.580 --> 00:08:03.500
Well, don't pout about it.

60
00:08:03.500 --> 00:08:04.710
Take a good look at this.

61
00:08:06.130 --> 00:08:14.680
I'd like to thank you for
the opportunity to visit this island.

62
00:08:15.850 --> 00:08:19.850
Dorry the Blue Ogre and Brogy the Red Ogre
of the Giant Warrior Pirates.

63
00:08:20.650 --> 00:08:23.070
There are old tales about them.

64
00:08:23.070 --> 00:08:25.360
This is a wanted poster
from 100 years ago!

65
00:08:25.360 --> 00:08:30.780
And now they reside here
on this very island.

66
00:08:30.780 --> 00:08:34.870
To this day, a 100-million-berry bounty
is on each of their heads.

67
00:08:34.870 --> 00:08:37.580
That's 200 million berries
for the both of them.

68
00:08:37.580 --> 00:08:39.620
A 200-million-berry payout?

69
00:08:39.620 --> 00:08:42.000
Regardless, they're giants.

70
00:08:42.460 --> 00:08:48.470
Only the most superb minds
execute the most superb crimes.

71
00:08:48.470 --> 00:08:52.220
All you have to do
is follow my instructions.

72
00:08:52.220 --> 00:08:58.890
With a little ingenuity,
we can even cut through mountains.

73
00:09:21.080 --> 00:09:24.380
Dorry! I got us some booze,
courtesy of our guests.

74
00:09:24.790 --> 00:09:25.920
Great!

75
00:09:25.920 --> 00:09:29.170
It's been a while since
my last drink. I'd love some.

76
00:09:37.390 --> 00:09:38.350
I see.

77
00:09:38.350 --> 00:09:41.560
His guests are your friends, huh?

78
00:09:41.560 --> 00:09:44.730
I saw a long-nosed man
and a woman.

79
00:09:44.730 --> 00:09:46.360
That's Usopp and Nami!

80
00:09:46.360 --> 00:09:49.360
How funny! They said
they weren't leaving the ship.

81
00:09:49.360 --> 00:09:51.070
They do like adventures!

82
00:09:51.400 --> 00:09:55.740
Then, in a way, you could also say
that I got this alcohol from you.

83
00:09:58.200 --> 00:09:59.870
By the way, Dorry,

84
00:09:59.870 --> 00:10:03.420
is it true that the log takes
an entire year to register?

85
00:10:03.420 --> 00:10:09.130
Why... didn't you notice
the human skulls lying around?

86
00:10:10.260 --> 00:10:15.470
Most people who come to this island
die before their log is ready.

87
00:10:15.470 --> 00:10:17.560
Some are eaten by dinosaurs.

88
00:10:17.560 --> 00:10:20.100
Others starve or succumb to the heat.

89
00:10:20.100 --> 00:10:25.060
And some are killed when they attack us.
Indeed, all who come here die.

90
00:10:26.440 --> 00:10:32.030
It seems that one year on this island
is too long for humans.

91
00:10:32.740 --> 00:10:34.200
Then what can we do?

92
00:10:34.570 --> 00:10:37.070
Even if we could survive for a year,

93
00:10:37.070 --> 00:10:40.950
if that much time passes, who knows
what will become of my country?

94
00:10:41.580 --> 00:10:45.460
Yeah, it'd start to get pretty boring
if we stayed an entire year.

95
00:10:45.460 --> 00:10:47.750
Isn't there something
we can do, old guy?

96
00:10:49.420 --> 00:10:55.090
We do have an eternal pose,
but it's to our hometown, Elbaph.

97
00:10:55.090 --> 00:11:00.060
You could even say we're
fighting for this eternal pose.

98
00:11:00.060 --> 00:11:02.680
Do you want to try taking it by force?

99
00:11:02.680 --> 00:11:04.230
Not really.

100
00:11:04.230 --> 00:11:06.520
That's not where we wanna go.

101
00:11:06.900 --> 00:11:09.610
We just wanna go
to the island after this one.

102
00:11:09.610 --> 00:11:10.400
Right?

103
00:11:10.400 --> 00:11:11.190
That's right.

104
00:11:11.980 --> 00:11:16.200
If we lose the route to Alabasta,
there's no point in moving forward.

105
00:11:16.200 --> 00:11:17.360
See what I mean?

106
00:11:18.280 --> 00:11:21.160
Then why not pick
a heading and set sail?

107
00:11:21.790 --> 00:11:25.830
If luck is on your side,
you'll reach your destination.

108
00:11:32.500 --> 00:11:34.010
Maybe we'll do that!

109
00:11:36.680 --> 00:11:38.470
Who knows? We just might make it.

110
00:11:42.260 --> 00:11:47.100
You know, long ago, someone did leave
before the log was ready.

111
00:11:47.100 --> 00:11:48.440
What happened to him?

112
00:11:48.440 --> 00:11:50.190
How should I know?

113
00:11:50.190 --> 00:11:52.730
He must've gotten to the next island.

114
00:11:52.730 --> 00:11:54.030
That must be it!

115
00:11:57.910 --> 00:12:00.160
What's so funny?

116
00:12:06.660 --> 00:12:10.880
How can they laugh about
being stuck on this island?

117
00:12:16.720 --> 00:12:19.470
A brave warrior of the sea?

118
00:12:19.470 --> 00:12:20.470
What's that?

119
00:12:20.840 --> 00:12:22.720
I'm talking about you two!

120
00:12:22.720 --> 00:12:25.140
I wanna be just like you someday.

121
00:12:26.770 --> 00:12:27.730
You mean a giant?

122
00:12:28.350 --> 00:12:28.980
See?

123
00:12:28.980 --> 00:12:30.440
That's not it!

124
00:12:31.690 --> 00:12:36.400
I hope to live proudly
just like the warriors of Elbaph!

125
00:12:41.070 --> 00:12:41.740
So, that's it!

126
00:12:42.780 --> 00:12:46.450
We live so much longer
than you humans,

127
00:12:46.450 --> 00:12:49.540
so we often ponder
how we will die.

128
00:12:49.540 --> 00:12:55.050
Your assets, your life...
All will eventually cease to exist.

129
00:12:55.050 --> 00:13:00.510
But if we die as warriors of Elbaph
with our pride intact,

130
00:13:00.510 --> 00:13:02.390
that's an honorable death.

131
00:13:03.050 --> 00:13:07.850
That legacy is an everlasting treasure
passed down through generations in Elbaph.

132
00:13:09.350 --> 00:13:11.350
So, your treasure is your legacy?

133
00:13:11.350 --> 00:13:12.810
That's so cool!

134
00:13:12.810 --> 00:13:14.320
I've decided!

135
00:13:14.320 --> 00:13:17.230
From now on, I will call you master!

136
00:13:17.230 --> 00:13:18.360
Huh?

137
00:13:36.170 --> 00:13:37.250
Giant old guy!

138
00:13:40.130 --> 00:13:41.800
What's going on?!

139
00:13:41.800 --> 00:13:43.930
Why did his drink explode?

140
00:13:44.430 --> 00:13:47.890
That alcohol came
from our ship, didn't it?!

141
00:13:50.020 --> 00:13:52.230
It exploded in his stomach!

142
00:13:52.230 --> 00:13:55.110
That other giant must have
rigged it to explode!

143
00:13:55.810 --> 00:13:57.940
Were you even watching
the same fight?!

144
00:13:57.940 --> 00:14:01.400
After 100 years of fighting,
they'd never do something like this!

145
00:14:02.700 --> 00:14:04.910
Then who in the world…?

146
00:14:07.700 --> 00:14:09.540
You bastards did.

147
00:14:11.960 --> 00:14:14.250
It wasn't Brogy.

148
00:14:14.920 --> 00:14:20.510
We are proud warriors
that hail from Elbaph.

149
00:14:20.510 --> 00:14:25.220
Other than you,
who else is there to suspect?

150
00:14:26.220 --> 00:14:27.640
We need to run!

151
00:14:27.640 --> 00:14:29.600
Talking to him won't be of any use!

152
00:14:29.600 --> 00:14:31.600
Probably just as useless to run.

153
00:14:32.390 --> 00:14:34.060
Hold this and stay back.

154
00:14:35.060 --> 00:14:37.940
You can't mean…
You plan on fighting him?

155
00:14:41.280 --> 00:14:45.360
Sorry 'bout this, old guy,
but I need to shut you up.

156
00:14:49.870 --> 00:14:52.620
Both of you, stop! Please!

157
00:14:52.620 --> 00:14:54.290
Dorry, please listen!

158
00:14:54.290 --> 00:14:56.080
We're in the dark about this too!

159
00:14:56.080 --> 00:14:57.880
We're clueless about the explosion!

160
00:14:57.880 --> 00:14:59.090
Please don't fight!

161
00:14:59.460 --> 00:15:03.340
You need to stay put!
Your insides are in bad shape right now!

162
00:15:04.760 --> 00:15:10.180
How dare you...
do something so detestable!

163
00:15:21.190 --> 00:15:23.740
Gum-Gum...

164
00:15:41.130 --> 00:15:42.710
Gum-Gum...

165
00:15:52.810 --> 00:15:53.640
I'm sorry.

166
00:15:53.640 --> 00:15:55.600
Rocket!

167
00:16:24.090 --> 00:16:25.460
Luffy!

168
00:16:25.460 --> 00:16:27.630
So he has...

169
00:16:28.930 --> 00:16:31.350
the powers of a devil fruit.

170
00:16:32.180 --> 00:16:35.970
I underestimated... him...

171
00:16:55.620 --> 00:16:57.830
Luffy! Are you all right?

172
00:16:59.210 --> 00:17:00.170
How's the old guy?

173
00:17:01.000 --> 00:17:02.540
I think… he'll live.

174
00:17:02.920 --> 00:17:06.210
You made the right call.
He might not have calmed down.

175
00:17:08.090 --> 00:17:09.470
I'm really ticked off!

176
00:17:09.970 --> 00:17:11.220
Huh?

177
00:17:11.220 --> 00:17:16.470
Like the old guy said, the other giant
wouldn't have blown up the alcohol,

178
00:17:16.470 --> 00:17:20.140
and my friends would never do
a stupid thing like that!

179
00:17:20.770 --> 00:17:22.600
Then who could have...?

180
00:17:22.980 --> 00:17:25.730
There's someone else on this island.

181
00:17:34.280 --> 00:17:40.710
In essence, mental anguish
sways the outcomes of conflicts.

182
00:17:40.710 --> 00:17:43.130
Confusion has set in,

183
00:17:43.130 --> 00:17:48.590
all thanks to a mysterious bomb
served by an invisible foe.

184
00:17:49.260 --> 00:17:53.510
Now, regarding our first target,
Dorry the Blue Ogre,

185
00:17:53.510 --> 00:17:56.100
I already knew
we couldn't finish him off,

186
00:17:56.100 --> 00:17:59.930
but the damage his stomach received
must have been considerable.

187
00:17:59.930 --> 00:18:06.860
So, let us enjoy our tea
and await the start of the next duel.

188
00:18:07.320 --> 00:18:11.360
And, what, we let the other giant
finish off the injured one?

189
00:18:12.200 --> 00:18:14.490
That is precisely what we will do.

190
00:18:14.490 --> 00:18:16.330
No direct confrontation?

191
00:18:16.740 --> 00:18:21.500
That's because these warrior types
act exactly like wild boars.

192
00:18:21.500 --> 00:18:26.790
If we avoid a direct confrontation,
we can fight with minimal risk.

193
00:18:26.790 --> 00:18:29.380
We may be outmatched
in raw strength,

194
00:18:29.380 --> 00:18:32.880
but our brain power
more than compensates for it.

195
00:18:46.690 --> 00:18:48.110
Seriously...

196
00:18:48.520 --> 00:18:51.820
Can't you get it on your own,
Miss Golden Week?

197
00:18:52.400 --> 00:18:55.570
Out of curiosity, what's the plan
with the Straw Hat gang?

198
00:18:55.570 --> 00:19:01.290
Straw Hat...? Oh, the small-timers
who discovered the boss's secret.

199
00:19:01.870 --> 00:19:05.710
We will lure them out one by one,
starting with the easiest among them,

200
00:19:06.500 --> 00:19:09.290
right to my service set.

201
00:19:10.380 --> 00:19:14.800
My motto: Wicked deeds are
best served with a dash of foul play.

202
00:19:16.760 --> 00:19:20.970
There are countless ways to defeat
your enemies without lifting a finger.

203
00:19:25.560 --> 00:19:28.020
That mountain... Isn't it...?

204
00:19:33.820 --> 00:19:35.360
There's the signal.

205
00:19:36.530 --> 00:19:38.570
It's quite active today!

206
00:19:38.570 --> 00:19:41.660
Y-You're going?! Your wounds
from that last battle still haven't–

207
00:19:43.830 --> 00:19:44.960
Neither have his!

208
00:19:44.960 --> 00:19:47.460
We're both in the same condition!

209
00:19:51.670 --> 00:19:56.880
Making excuses during a fight
to the death would disgrace my name!

210
00:20:04.060 --> 00:20:05.140
Hey! Wait, old guy!

211
00:20:05.770 --> 00:20:06.810
Don't go!

212
00:20:06.810 --> 00:20:09.270
You can't go, Dorry!
You need to keep still!

213
00:20:09.270 --> 00:20:11.400
You'll die if you
push yourself too hard!

214
00:20:13.860 --> 00:20:17.150
I, the warrior Dorry, am here.

215
00:20:17.150 --> 00:20:18.240
At the very least...

216
00:20:19.410 --> 00:20:22.330
I will fight to uphold
the name of Elbaph!

217
00:20:25.700 --> 00:20:28.540
All right, Master Brogy! Good luck!

218
00:20:33.420 --> 00:20:35.300
You got it, Usopp!

219
00:20:35.300 --> 00:20:38.220
I'm gonna wipe the floor
with him for sure this time!

220
00:20:38.220 --> 00:20:41.600
Go get him, warrior of Elbaph!

221
00:20:44.350 --> 00:20:46.390
You've got this!

222
00:20:46.390 --> 00:20:48.140
You're great!

223
00:20:48.140 --> 00:20:50.150
You're awesome!

224
00:20:50.150 --> 00:20:51.650
You're powerful!

225
00:20:51.650 --> 00:20:53.770
You're huge!

226
00:20:53.770 --> 00:20:56.280
You're big! You're me!

227
00:20:54.400 --> 00:20:56.280
Going back to his pointless duel?

228
00:20:56.280 --> 00:20:58.450
A pointless duel?! You heathen!

229
00:20:58.450 --> 00:21:01.780
Brogy's a brave warrior of the sea!
I plan to be just like him!

230
00:21:01.780 --> 00:21:04.740
What gives you the right to...?!

231
00:21:02.780 --> 00:21:04.740
Anyway, let's get back to the ship.

232
00:21:05.620 --> 00:21:09.370
We are not staying a year
just for the log to register!

233
00:21:09.370 --> 00:21:11.630
We'll regroup on the ship
to figure this out.

234
00:21:11.630 --> 00:21:13.040
Hold it! Not so fast!

235
00:21:15.550 --> 00:21:19.050
I am absolutely useless
in a fight against dinosaurs!

236
00:21:19.050 --> 00:21:23.760
As such, we cannot possibly
traverse the jungle to reach our ship!

237
00:21:24.430 --> 00:21:28.310
Then what was all that about
being a "brave warrior of the sea?"

238
00:21:28.310 --> 00:21:30.940
You caught me thinking out loud!

239
00:21:30.940 --> 00:21:34.150
I want to become a man
who's proud of the way he lives!

240
00:21:34.560 --> 00:21:35.820
No choice then.

241
00:21:35.820 --> 00:21:39.150
Luffy's party is
at the other giant's house.

242
00:21:39.150 --> 00:21:41.110
We'll just have to head there.

243
00:21:41.400 --> 00:21:42.740
Listen, Nami.

244
00:21:42.740 --> 00:21:45.620
Someday down the road,
if I wind up losing everything,

245
00:21:45.620 --> 00:21:49.120
and greet death all alone
on a deserted island,

246
00:21:49.120 --> 00:21:52.500
as I lay dying, I will proudly proclaim:

247
00:21:52.500 --> 00:21:56.250
"I am Usopp!
Brave warrior of the sea!"

248
00:21:58.130 --> 00:21:59.170
Yeah, yeah.

249
00:21:59.800 --> 00:22:03.130
Then will you hurry it up
and get your warrior act together?

250
00:22:03.130 --> 00:22:04.510
Oh...

251
00:22:04.510 --> 00:22:05.600
Yeah!

252
00:22:12.600 --> 00:22:14.060
What are you doing, old guy?!

253
00:22:14.060 --> 00:22:15.980
Get this rock off me! Hey!

254
00:22:15.980 --> 00:22:17.820
We can't stop.

255
00:22:21.070 --> 00:22:24.200
Over 100 years ago...

256
00:22:26.240 --> 00:22:28.990
we commenced our fight.

257
00:22:30.910 --> 00:22:35.710
But if I abandon
a battle that I started,

258
00:22:35.710 --> 00:22:38.550
I would abandon the right
to call myself a warrior.

259
00:22:39.130 --> 00:22:41.920
If I am no longer a warrior,

260
00:22:41.920 --> 00:22:45.090
I will cease to be me.

261
00:22:46.430 --> 00:22:49.680
I was wrong to suspect you.

262
00:22:50.810 --> 00:22:53.350
Heaven has censured me.

263
00:22:54.900 --> 00:22:58.110
Elbaph, the god of war,
has decided my fate.

264
00:22:59.270 --> 00:23:01.230
I didn't have his divine protection.

265
00:23:01.230 --> 00:23:03.360
That is all.

266
00:23:05.450 --> 00:23:10.620
Gods?! Divine protection?!
None of that stuff matters!

267
00:23:10.620 --> 00:23:13.160
You'd die just because
some god told you to?!

268
00:23:13.870 --> 00:23:16.250
Someone is trying
to mess with your duel!

269
00:23:17.420 --> 00:23:19.460
It's not a fair fight!

270
00:23:19.460 --> 00:23:20.750
This duel's over!

271
00:23:21.500 --> 00:23:22.510
I'm right, aren't I?!

272
00:23:22.510 --> 00:23:24.720
Be quiet!

273
00:23:26.510 --> 00:23:31.470
You've only lived a mere
ten or twenty years.

274
00:23:31.470 --> 00:23:35.520
Elbaph's divine teachings
wouldn't resonate with you.

275
00:23:36.350 --> 00:23:37.850
Who gives a crap about that?!

276
00:23:37.850 --> 00:23:40.020
Hey! Move this thing!

277
00:23:40.020 --> 00:23:41.320
Hey! Old guy!

278
00:23:41.320 --> 00:23:45.530
Hey! Old guy! Hey! Dammit!

279
00:23:45.950 --> 00:23:47.410
It won't budge!

280
00:23:56.250 --> 00:23:57.290
Dorry!

281
00:23:57.290 --> 00:23:59.920
How was your drink?!
Hit the spot, didn't it?!

282
00:24:00.920 --> 00:24:01.920
Yeah.

283
00:24:01.920 --> 00:24:03.510
Truly the nectar of the gods.

284
00:24:06.090 --> 00:24:08.640
Overstating things a bit,
I see! Let's go!

285
00:24:16.100 --> 00:24:18.480
What's wrong, Dorry?!

286
00:24:18.480 --> 00:24:20.480
You're a bit sluggish!

287
00:24:21.730 --> 00:24:24.360
Don't kid yourself!
I'm the same as ever!

288
00:24:28.780 --> 00:24:31.320
Move, you stupid thing! Come on!

289
00:24:32.280 --> 00:24:35.540
Just when I've gone and met
such an awesome warrior!

290
00:24:36.370 --> 00:24:37.500
Luffy...

291
00:24:39.210 --> 00:24:43.210
Why would he go this far
for a giant he just met?

292
00:24:43.210 --> 00:24:46.720
It's out of character for a crook
with a bounty on his head.

293
00:24:46.720 --> 00:24:47.970
Who was it?!

294
00:24:47.970 --> 00:24:51.050
Who messed with the giants' duel?!

295
00:24:52.680 --> 00:24:54.220
Oh, come to think of it...

296
00:24:55.640 --> 00:24:56.730
Karoo is gone!

297
00:25:05.190 --> 00:25:07.570
Damn. I'm lost.

298
00:25:08.490 --> 00:25:11.820
I at least recognize this tree.

299
00:25:11.820 --> 00:25:15.290
I'm sure it was a left
at the tree wrapped in vines.

300
00:25:16.490 --> 00:25:18.540
Oh! It's you, Nami!

301
00:25:19.160 --> 00:25:21.000
Perfect timing!

302
00:25:21.000 --> 00:25:24.170
See, I sorta lost my way,
so I wasn't sure what to do.

303
00:25:24.670 --> 00:25:27.050
What are you doing here, anyway?

304
00:25:28.300 --> 00:25:29.130
Hey.

305
00:25:29.130 --> 00:25:30.380
What's the deal?

306
00:25:34.930 --> 00:25:36.890
Dinosaur!

307
00:25:36.890 --> 00:25:38.890
Dinosaur! Dinosaur! Dinosaur!

308
00:25:41.730 --> 00:25:43.610
Hey, you! You're going too fast!

309
00:25:46.570 --> 00:25:48.280
That guy...

310
00:25:48.820 --> 00:25:49.780
Luffy!

311
00:25:50.360 --> 00:25:51.910
What a relief!

312
00:25:51.910 --> 00:25:54.070
What are you doing here?

313
00:26:07.920 --> 00:26:09.550
Nami?

314
00:26:20.350 --> 00:26:23.810
Nami! Nami! Nami! Nami!

315
00:26:25.190 --> 00:26:26.980
This is bad.

316
00:26:26.980 --> 00:26:31.530
Luffy!
